<ArticleLayout
  title="Newborn Essentials for First-Time Parents"
  description="A practical Australian guide to the items that tend to matter most in the first few months, with notes on what can wait."
  category="Nursery & Kids"
  date="Updated July 2026"
  readingTime="8 minute read"
  image="/images/Nursery-kids.webp"
  imageAlt="A tidy nursery room with timber furniture, soft lighting and practical baby storage"
>
  <p>
    Preparing for a newborn can feel like being handed a very long list at the exact moment
    your brain would prefer a cup of tea and a lie down. The useful starting point is simpler:
    focus on safe sleep, feeding, nappies, washing, transport and a few comfortable clothes.
  </p>
  <p>
    This guide is not a checklist to finish in one weekend. It is a way to sort essentials
    from nice-to-haves so you can prepare your home without overfilling the nursery.
  </p>

  <h2>The core newborn essentials</h2>
  <div class="grid two">
    <ProductCard
      label="Sleep"
      title="A safe sleep space"
      description="Choose a cot or bassinet that suits your room, has a firm mattress and uses fitted sheets made for that exact size."
      note="Keep pillows, loose blankets and decorative soft items out of the sleep space."
    />
    <ProductCard
      label="Changing"
      title="Nappies and a practical change setup"
      description="You can use a dedicated change table, a secure mat on a dresser or another stable surface that keeps supplies within reach."
    />
    <ProductCard
      label="Clothing"
      title="Simple layers"
      description="Zip suits, singlets, socks and season-appropriate layers are usually easier than fussy outfits in the early weeks."
    />
    <ProductCard
      label="Outings"
      title="A way to travel safely"
      description="Plan for a correctly fitted car restraint and a pram or carrier that suits your home, transport and local footpaths."
    />
  </div>

  <h2>What can usually wait</h2>
  <p>
    Many nursery extras are lovely but not urgent. Monitors, bottle warmers, wipe warmers,
    large toy collections, decorative bedding and specialist organisers may become useful,
    but they are rarely the difference between prepared and unprepared.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you are considering a monitor, compare whether you need audio, video or app access,
    and check camera placement, cord safety, range, battery life and privacy settings.
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2>Australian home considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Think about summer heat, winter room temperature, rental limitations, storage space and
    how often you will need to move items between rooms. A compact, washable setup can be
    more useful than a picture-perfect nursery that only works in one corner.
  </p>
  <p>
    For safety-sensitive items such as sleep spaces and car restraints, check current advice
    from recognised Australian authorities and follow the product instructions carefully.
    Second-hand can be practical for some items, but avoid anything with missing labels,
    unknown history, damage or incomplete parts.
  </p>

  <h2>Helpful Australian safety references</h2>
  <p>
    For current guidance, start with{" "}
    <ExternalLink href="https://rednose.org.au/safe-sleep-and-safer-pregnancy/overview/">Red Nose safe sleep advice</ExternalLink>,{" "}
    <ExternalLink href="https://www.productsafety.gov.au/">Product Safety Australia</ExternalLink>{" "}
    and{" "}
    <ExternalLink href="https://www.childcarseats.com.au/">Child Car Seats Australia</ExternalLink>.
    Use these resources alongside product instructions and professional fitting support where
    relevant.
  </p>

  <h2>A calmer first list</h2>
  <ul class="feature-list">
    <li>Safe sleep space, fitted sheets and season-appropriate sleepwear.</li>
    <li>Nappies, wipes, barrier cream and a stable changing surface.</li>
    <li>Several easy-change outfits in practical sizes.</li>
    <li>Feeding supplies that match your planned approach, with room to adjust later.</li>
    <li>Baby bath basics, soft towels and gentle laundry planning.</li>
    <li>Correctly fitted car restraint before the first trip home.</li>
  </ul>

  <FAQBlock items={faqs} />
  <RelatedGuidesBlock guides={relatedGuides} />
</ArticleLayout>
